  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to describe the treatments received and outcomes of patients
      with metastatic colorectal cancer, what percentage of these patients have K-Ras mutation of
      the tumor, and to describe the costs of treatments. Information will also be collected
      regarding risk factors, variables among treatment centers and patients, and explorative
      analyses will be done to try to identify factors that impact prognosis and factors that
      predict tolerability and response to treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
